1
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:51,885
Write them on paper.

2
00:00:52,322 --> 00:00:53,682
Please, we’re running out of time!

3
00:00:54,054 --> 00:00:55,555
Don’t you get it, Lorelei?

4
00:00:59,309 --> 00:01:00,935
How do we crack the code?

5
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:03,271
Only Loki can do that!

6
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:05,774
I'm not the suspect.

7
00:01:19,996 --> 00:01:20,996
Well...

8
00:01:21,831 --> 00:01:23,291
what did you expect from me?

9
00:01:28,296 --> 00:01:31,799
And you’re saying
I was just offended by what you did,

10
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:33,051
which you think wasn’t wrong?

11
00:01:38,098 --> 00:01:39,241
Where’s the rest of his team?

12
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,893
And I clearly heard him dial that number.

13
00:01:42,143 --> 00:01:43,520
It came from his phone.

14
00:02:01,246 --> 00:02:02,705
Officer Montreal.

15
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:05,582
Are you okay?

16
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:09,754
Yes, of course!

17
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:13,091
How can we help you?

18
00:02:14,884 --> 00:02:17,512
Chief wants to consult something
with you guys.

19
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:20,223
Would it be okay
if I discuss it properly first?

20
00:02:22,517 --> 00:02:23,517
Alright.

21
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:28,523
Is Chief busy again,
so he sent you here again?

22
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:31,276
Is he handling a much more important case?

23
00:02:32,026 --> 00:02:33,278
Something like that.

24
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:37,114
That’s why I’m always the one
he sends to hand things out,

25
00:02:37,115 --> 00:02:39,576
deliver, or call someone.

26
00:02:40,118 --> 00:02:42,370
So, how can we help you?

27
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,664
We received a missing person report
the other day.

28
00:02:45,665 --> 00:02:47,250
A female student.

29
00:02:47,333 --> 00:02:50,503
Apparently, she hasn’t been home
for two days.

30
00:02:52,463 --> 00:02:53,673
So you want us to find her?

31
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:55,591
She might have just eloped
with her boyfriend

32
00:02:55,592 --> 00:02:56,925
or run away from home

33
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:58,761
to get away from her abusive parents.

34
00:02:59,137 --> 00:03:01,513
Actually, there’s no need
to look for her anymore.

35
00:03:01,514 --> 00:03:03,141
She was found last night.

36
00:03:03,558 --> 00:03:04,726
If that’s the case,

37
00:03:05,351 --> 00:03:06,603
what do you still need from us?

38
00:03:07,312 --> 00:03:08,312
Oh!

39
00:03:08,479 --> 00:03:10,106
I think I should clarify something...

40
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:12,650
She was found, but...

41
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:16,905
she was found dead
in an abandoned building near campus.

42
00:03:17,238 --> 00:03:18,989
Her body was found burned.

43
00:03:18,990 --> 00:03:22,285
She was barely recognizable
if not for her things scattered around.

44
00:03:22,785 --> 00:03:24,204
And what’s the tablet for?

45
00:03:24,996 --> 00:03:27,039
Someone posted about it on social media.

46
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,625
An anonymous user.

47
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,793
He posted this video. Take a look.

48
00:04:10,662 --> 00:04:12,914
♪ Shadows ♪

49
00:04:13,206 --> 00:04:15,917
♪ in the dark are crawling. ♪

50
00:04:16,599 --> 00:04:20,671
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way. ♪

51
00:04:20,672 --> 00:04:24,217
♪ As if the line could not be crossed. ♪

52
00:04:25,176 --> 00:04:28,762
♪ To every scream and every tremor. ♪

53
00:04:28,763 --> 00:04:31,932
♪ These walls remain the only witness. ♪

54
00:04:31,933 --> 00:04:34,893
♪ Every noise is etched in here. ♪

55
00:04:34,894 --> 00:04:39,399
♪ Like fire and ammunition for your memory. ♪

56
00:04:40,775 --> 00:04:42,902
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

57
00:04:44,154 --> 00:04:46,531
♪ The threats poised to strike. ♪

58
00:04:47,615 --> 00:04:51,286
♪ For this world ♪

59
00:04:51,953 --> 00:04:54,580
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

60
00:04:54,581 --> 00:04:57,042
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

61
00:04:58,043 --> 00:05:00,170
♪ Open up your eyes. ♪

62
00:05:01,463 --> 00:05:05,008
♪ For this world ♪

63
00:05:05,717 --> 00:05:08,260
♪ is not what you imagined. ♪

64
00:05:08,261 --> 00:05:13,099
♪ Heed the warnings. ♪

65
00:05:14,261 --> 00:05:15,470
That’s enough!

66
00:05:16,997 --> 00:05:17,873
That’s enough!

67
00:05:17,898 --> 00:05:20,024
Why did we even have to watch that video?

68
00:05:20,546 --> 00:05:22,673
The video’s already been taken down
from social media.

69
00:05:22,835 --> 00:05:24,753
Good thing we downloaded it right away.

70
00:05:25,003 --> 00:05:27,130
This is solid evidence for the case.

71
00:05:27,451 --> 00:05:30,411
The girl in that video is Faye Figueroa.

72
00:05:30,436 --> 00:05:32,188
She's the missing student.

73
00:05:32,772 --> 00:05:35,149
With all the resources
of the campus police,

74
00:05:35,900 --> 00:05:37,735
you can solve this case on your own.

75
00:05:38,569 --> 00:05:40,363
Why do you still need our help?

76
00:05:40,947 --> 00:05:42,740
According to our lead,

77
00:05:43,032 --> 00:05:45,993
they say one of Faye’s orgmates did this.

78
00:05:46,702 --> 00:05:47,702
Org?

79
00:05:47,912 --> 00:05:51,833
Yes, Faye was part
of a student executive committee.

80
00:05:52,041 --> 00:05:53,167
The execom?

81
00:05:54,335 --> 00:05:57,755
Aren’t they supposed to be
the student council’s right hand?

82
00:05:59,048 --> 00:06:01,007
They’re a group of student volunteers

83
00:06:01,008 --> 00:06:03,386
always assigned to run errands
during events.

84
00:06:04,512 --> 00:06:05,679
Yes, you're right.

85
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,932
That’s why we need your help here.

86
00:06:08,224 --> 00:06:10,642
We can investigate
the suspect in the execom,

87
00:06:10,643 --> 00:06:12,687
but if we do,

88
00:06:13,187 --> 00:06:14,856
it’ll draw too much attention.

89
00:06:15,314 --> 00:06:18,733
That’s why Chief thought maybe
you could handle the investigation,

90
00:06:18,734 --> 00:06:20,945
so people wouldn’t get alarmed.

91
00:06:21,779 --> 00:06:23,739
Didn’t you say you already have a lead?

92
00:06:24,490 --> 00:06:26,701
Can you tell us who the suspect is?

93
00:06:27,702 --> 00:06:29,412
This is Hector Alvarez.

94
00:06:30,329 --> 00:06:32,039
He was with Faye in the execom.

95
00:06:32,874 --> 00:06:34,583
He’s also the one being pointed to
as the prime suspect

96
00:06:34,584 --> 00:06:36,169
by the victim’s parents.

97
00:06:36,377 --> 00:06:37,712
He was Faye’s boyfriend, and...

98
00:06:37,962 --> 00:06:41,007
possibly the last person seen with her
before she disappeared.

99
00:06:41,424 --> 00:06:43,009
I know you think he looks innocent.

100
00:06:44,260 --> 00:06:47,972
But by now you should know
that looks can really be deceiving.

101
00:06:49,182 --> 00:06:50,349
Alvarez…

102
00:06:52,018 --> 00:06:54,228
Does he have any connection to our mayor?

103
00:06:54,645 --> 00:06:55,645
Yes.

104
00:06:55,646 --> 00:06:58,566
He’s Mayor Vicente Alvarez’s nephew.

105
00:07:00,902 --> 00:07:04,405
So that’s why the Chief didn’t
directly involve the campus police yet.

106
00:07:04,655 --> 00:07:06,741
He doesn’t want to be singled out
by the mayor.

107
00:07:07,450 --> 00:07:08,451
And of course,

108
00:07:09,035 --> 00:07:11,329
he’s also careful not to ruin
the university’s name.

109
00:07:12,163 --> 00:07:13,163
Good move.

110
00:07:13,247 --> 00:07:14,706
That’s why, as much as possible,

111
00:07:14,707 --> 00:07:17,835
Chief wants to keep
this investigation discreet for now.

112
00:07:18,419 --> 00:07:23,090
You were the first people he thought of,
trusting you with this request.

113
00:07:23,549 --> 00:07:24,717
Don’t worry, officer.

114
00:07:25,134 --> 00:07:26,260
We’ll take it from here.

115
00:07:26,844 --> 00:07:29,138
Expect to hear from us anytime today.

116
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,640
May we get your number

117
00:07:30,641 --> 00:07:32,850
so we can contact you
for any developments?

118
00:07:37,271 --> 00:07:40,525
Alright, I should get going.
The investigation’s about to start.

119
00:07:42,443 --> 00:07:43,443
Thank you.

120
00:08:00,169 --> 00:08:01,379
Hurry up and eat.

121
00:08:02,213 --> 00:08:05,550
We need to carry out the investigation
while it’s still break time.

122
00:08:06,133 --> 00:08:07,884
The sooner we close this case,

123
00:08:07,885 --> 00:08:10,930
the sooner we can focus our collective
attention on the rookie officer.

124
00:08:11,264 --> 00:08:12,264
So what’s the plan?

125
00:08:12,682 --> 00:08:15,685
You two will visit the Office
of the Student Executive Committee.

126
00:08:15,977 --> 00:08:19,647
While I will check the security footage
on the day of the victim’s disappearance.

127
00:08:21,190 --> 00:08:23,943
Can I just go with you instead, Loki?

128
00:08:24,527 --> 00:08:27,822
I’ll learn a lot more if I go with you.

129
00:08:27,863 --> 00:08:30,408
I need to learn from the best!

130
00:08:36,122 --> 00:08:37,582
You have nothing to worry, Jamie.

131
00:08:37,915 --> 00:08:40,084
Lorelei is a capable detective-in-training.

132
00:08:41,669 --> 00:08:43,337
You can learn a thing or two from her.

133
00:08:43,379 --> 00:08:46,716
Besides, Lorelei needs you there more...

134
00:08:47,758 --> 00:08:50,469
since you remind Margarette
of someone close to her.

135
00:08:52,263 --> 00:08:53,263
Let’s go.

136
00:08:53,347 --> 00:08:54,682
We'll meet again later.

137
00:09:02,898 --> 00:09:05,318
It’s you and me again.

138
00:09:05,818 --> 00:09:08,112
It feels like déjà vu, right?

139
00:09:08,529 --> 00:09:11,448
Come on, Jamie.
Now is not the time to trade barbs.

140
00:09:11,449 --> 00:09:14,409
If you don’t wanna come with me,
then stay here.

141
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:16,286
Oh, come on, Lorelei!

142
00:09:16,287 --> 00:09:18,456
Will you manage without me?

143
00:09:19,290 --> 00:09:21,208
I don’t think so.

144
00:09:22,501 --> 00:09:24,378
Fine. Go ahead.

145
00:09:24,587 --> 00:09:25,671
Let’s go!

146
00:09:36,307 --> 00:09:37,516
Before we enter,

147
00:09:37,892 --> 00:09:39,935
have you come up with a brilliant plan?

148
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:42,800
Don’t tell me we’re just going
to walk in there like that?

149
00:09:45,066 --> 00:09:47,693
Actually, I haven’t thought of one yet.

150
00:09:47,735 --> 00:09:49,028
Gosh!

151
00:09:49,362 --> 00:09:51,988
It should’ve just been me and Loki
investigating this place,

152
00:09:51,989 --> 00:09:54,659
while you checked the security footage.

153
00:09:54,825 --> 00:09:58,119
You’d probably be more useful
for something that boring,

154
00:09:58,120 --> 00:10:00,122
since you’re a boring person anyway.

155
00:10:01,707 --> 00:10:02,792
You know what?

156
00:10:03,125 --> 00:10:04,960
Let’s just go back to Loki.

157
00:10:05,753 --> 00:10:08,547
Jamie! Get back here!

158
00:10:09,590 --> 00:10:10,675
Come on!

159
00:10:10,966 --> 00:10:12,301
Ooh...

160
00:10:12,635 --> 00:10:15,721
That’s a face I don’t get
to see here every day.

161
00:10:18,683 --> 00:10:20,226
What are you doing here?

162
00:10:20,810 --> 00:10:24,730
Do you have business with us,
or are you just lost?

163
00:10:25,147 --> 00:10:28,484
Isn’t the magnet of bad luck
with you today?

164
00:10:30,111 --> 00:10:31,111
- Well...
- Hi!

165
00:10:33,948 --> 00:10:35,281
We’re not lost.

166
00:10:35,282 --> 00:10:37,159
We came here on purpose.

167
00:10:41,122 --> 00:10:43,248
We’re here to investigate

168
00:10:43,249 --> 00:10:46,127
the disappearance and death
of an execom member.

169
00:10:47,044 --> 00:10:49,088
You mean, Faye Figueroa?

170
00:10:49,797 --> 00:10:52,466
And what does the Q.E.D. Club
have to do with her?

171
00:10:52,633 --> 00:10:54,593
Sorry, but it’s none of your business.

172
00:10:54,844 --> 00:10:58,221
And we’re here to talk to Hector Alvarez.

173
00:10:58,222 --> 00:11:00,181
But it’s definitely my business,

174
00:11:00,182 --> 00:11:02,977
because I’m the chairwoman
of the executive committee.

175
00:11:03,394 --> 00:11:04,687
And just so you know,

176
00:11:05,146 --> 00:11:09,191
the execom is already conducting
an internal inquiry about that matter,

177
00:11:09,275 --> 00:11:12,820
so external interference
is no longer needed.

178
00:11:13,571 --> 00:11:17,241
You can head back to your clubroom now
and just relax there.

179
00:11:17,825 --> 00:11:22,663
There’s nothing wrong with us doing
separate investigations, right?

180
00:11:23,247 --> 00:11:26,249
It’s better to have another set of eyes

181
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:28,919
looking at the case
from a different angle.

182
00:11:29,587 --> 00:11:31,422
That’s just my two cents.

183
00:11:34,258 --> 00:11:35,258
Fine.

184
00:11:35,551 --> 00:11:38,721
I’ll let you talk to Hector,
but you have to wait here.

185
00:11:38,971 --> 00:11:41,307
Unauthorized students
aren’t allowed inside.

186
00:11:41,932 --> 00:11:45,227
And by the way, this is a sensitive case.

187
00:11:45,519 --> 00:11:46,812
If you mess this up,

188
00:11:47,563 --> 00:11:49,982
everything we’ve worked for
will go to waste.

189
00:11:56,989 --> 00:11:58,157
Nice acting!

190
00:11:58,407 --> 00:12:01,786
Well, I’m not a theater actress
for nothing.

191
00:12:02,594 --> 00:12:04,346
And what I find strange is,

192
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:07,936
what’s with her reaction when she saw me?

193
00:12:08,501 --> 00:12:09,960
She's the same as Loki.

194
00:12:10,586 --> 00:12:12,630
Is there something wrong with my face?

195
00:12:14,256 --> 00:12:15,716
Your face is fine.

196
00:12:15,841 --> 00:12:16,926
It’s just that...

197
00:12:17,218 --> 00:12:20,304
you remind them
of their late friend, Rhea.

198
00:12:20,930 --> 00:12:23,933
You’ve got the same aura and style,

199
00:12:24,183 --> 00:12:26,018
especially that braided red hair.

200
00:12:27,770 --> 00:12:28,770
Really?

201
00:12:29,021 --> 00:12:33,067
I didn’t know that my looks
will bother them, especially Loki.

202
00:12:34,235 --> 00:12:35,861
Should I change my hairstyle?

203
00:12:38,864 --> 00:12:41,992
Excuse me, you wanted to talk to me?

204
00:12:42,785 --> 00:12:44,495
I’m Hector Alvarez.

205
00:12:45,621 --> 00:12:48,249
I’m Lorelei Rios. This is Jamie Santiago.

206
00:12:48,415 --> 00:12:49,959
We’re from the Q.E.D. Club.

207
00:12:50,626 --> 00:12:51,836
Q.E.D. Club?

208
00:12:52,795 --> 00:12:56,173
If you’re gonna ask me questions,
can we talk in the parking lot instead?

209
00:12:56,590 --> 00:13:01,220
Because Maggie asked us to buy
some materials for the redecoration.

210
00:13:01,929 --> 00:13:03,263
Sure! No problem.

211
00:13:03,264 --> 00:13:04,974
Okay. I’ll head there first, okay?

212
00:13:14,233 --> 00:13:15,734
He looks innocent.

213
00:13:16,318 --> 00:13:18,904
But for someone
who just lost his girlfriend,

214
00:13:20,322 --> 00:13:21,991
he seems so unbothered.

215
00:13:24,493 --> 00:13:25,493
Hector!

216
00:13:26,453 --> 00:13:28,664
Our condolences for Faye’s passing.

217
00:13:29,123 --> 00:13:33,210
But we’d like to ask you
a few questions about her.

218
00:13:46,557 --> 00:13:47,557
Why?

219
00:13:47,808 --> 00:13:50,311
Do you think I had something to do
with what happened to her?

220
00:13:51,061 --> 00:13:53,147
Do you think I could do that
to someone I love?

221
00:13:55,357 --> 00:13:56,358
I know...

222
00:13:56,859 --> 00:14:00,988
everyone thinks I’m not even affected
by what happened to her.

223
00:14:01,739 --> 00:14:03,032
But deep inside...

224
00:14:04,366 --> 00:14:06,076
I’m just keeping it all inside.

225
00:14:06,577 --> 00:14:07,577
I need to...

226
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:09,997
I need to force myself to be normal.

227
00:14:12,041 --> 00:14:14,251
So I don’t completely lose my mind.

228
00:14:15,085 --> 00:14:17,838
It’s not that we suspect you, Hector.

229
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:20,840
To be honest,
we’re interviewing everyone close to her

230
00:14:20,841 --> 00:14:23,385
so we can figure out
what really happened to her.

231
00:14:24,011 --> 00:14:26,512
We want to see the bigger picture

232
00:14:26,513 --> 00:14:29,683
so we can get an idea
of what really happened to Faye.

233
00:14:31,810 --> 00:14:33,437
What is it you want to know?

234
00:14:34,021 --> 00:14:38,525
The last time Faye was seen
was two days ago, is that right?

235
00:14:39,652 --> 00:14:40,652
Yeah.

236
00:14:40,778 --> 00:14:44,198
The last time I saw her
was after the noon break.

237
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:47,701
We were together
at the execom office then.

238
00:14:47,785 --> 00:14:51,497
Maggie asked us to handle some paperwork.

239
00:14:51,956 --> 00:14:53,832
Didn’t you meet after that?

240
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:58,379
We already went back
to the classroom after that.

241
00:14:58,587 --> 00:15:02,091
We actually agreed to just meet
here at the parking lot after that.

242
00:15:02,633 --> 00:15:06,178
To make things clearer,
this was our conversation.

243
00:16:08,949 --> 00:16:11,285
This was our last conversation
with each other.

244
00:16:12,619 --> 00:16:16,248
My guess is, whoever she was meeting
before we met up…

245
00:16:16,999 --> 00:16:20,878
might be the one
behind this horrific crime.

246
00:16:22,087 --> 00:16:25,424
Once I find out who did this to her…

247
00:16:27,092 --> 00:16:31,555
what’s coming for them
will be worse than a fire.

248
00:16:32,222 --> 00:16:34,975
Do you have any idea
who she was meeting that day?

249
00:16:35,684 --> 00:16:38,187
Faye never mentioned anything to me.

250
00:16:38,771 --> 00:16:41,565
But I have a feeling...

251
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:46,528
it might be the guy
I saw talking to her before.

252
00:16:47,321 --> 00:16:48,447
What makes you say that?

253
00:16:49,364 --> 00:16:50,741
Who was the guy?

254
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,743
Can you describe him to me?

255
00:16:53,786 --> 00:16:55,866
I don’t know, there was just
something off about him.

256
00:16:56,163 --> 00:16:59,458
I didn’t really get a good look
at his face, but…

257
00:17:00,793 --> 00:17:05,422
I remember he had a lollipop
in his mouth that time.

258
00:17:06,423 --> 00:17:08,217
It was actually pretty weird.

259
00:17:10,636 --> 00:17:13,013
I never got the chance
to ask Faye about it.

260
00:17:17,351 --> 00:17:20,062
If you still have more questions,

261
00:17:20,437 --> 00:17:23,732
you can just come see me
at the office later.

262
00:17:24,358 --> 00:17:25,984
I’ll still be coming back here anyway.

263
00:17:27,277 --> 00:17:31,490
I hope I was able to help
with your investigation somehow.

264
00:17:32,032 --> 00:17:33,032
Wait!

265
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,619
Can we get your number?

266
00:17:38,163 --> 00:17:39,414
Sure, no problem.

267
00:17:49,341 --> 00:17:50,341
Thank you.

268
00:18:21,039 --> 00:18:22,039
That’s her!

269
00:18:23,584 --> 00:18:24,584
That’s her.

270
00:18:27,421 --> 00:18:29,756
Let’s check the CCTV at the gate.

271
00:18:41,518 --> 00:18:42,811
Can you speed it up?

272
00:18:53,906 --> 00:18:55,574
He’s a damn good actor

273
00:18:56,074 --> 00:18:57,743
if he’s lying.

274
00:18:58,452 --> 00:19:00,329
It’s a believable story...

275
00:19:01,163 --> 00:19:03,624
but I’m not totally convinced.

276
00:19:04,541 --> 00:19:06,335
Something is off.

277
00:19:07,002 --> 00:19:09,671
Based on his message thread with Faye...

278
00:19:10,839 --> 00:19:13,175
their relationship seemed okay.

279
00:19:14,176 --> 00:19:17,429
But what possible motive

280
00:19:17,763 --> 00:19:19,890
could he have for hurting his girlfriend?

281
00:19:22,017 --> 00:19:25,854
That "suspicious guy" he keeps talking
about who's always with Faye,

282
00:19:26,605 --> 00:19:28,023
it sounds legit.

283
00:19:28,482 --> 00:19:31,400
Unless, he mentioned it

284
00:19:31,401 --> 00:19:34,112
just to divert our attention
away from him.

285
00:19:35,030 --> 00:19:38,367
Regardless,
he’s still our primary suspect.

286
00:19:38,492 --> 00:19:40,994
He can’t shake off
our suspicions so easily.

287
00:19:42,287 --> 00:19:44,498
I wonder what Loki’s found so far.

288
00:19:45,207 --> 00:19:48,085
I watched two videos
at the security office.

289
00:19:48,961 --> 00:19:52,421
The CCTV footage
from the school building entrance

290
00:19:52,422 --> 00:19:55,342
and the footage from the front gate.

291
00:19:59,513 --> 00:20:01,014
At 4:15 p.m.,

292
00:20:01,223 --> 00:20:04,101
the victim was last seen
leaving the building.

293
00:20:04,559 --> 00:20:07,688
But she was not seen leaving
the campus grounds through the gate.

294
00:20:08,021 --> 00:20:11,066
Didn’t the same thing happen
to Madonna Barcelon?

295
00:20:11,483 --> 00:20:12,858
Later on, we found out

296
00:20:12,859 --> 00:20:15,279
that she was killed
within the campus premises.

297
00:20:16,446 --> 00:20:18,115
Only this time it’s different.

298
00:20:19,032 --> 00:20:19,992
The now-deleted video

299
00:20:19,993 --> 00:20:23,328
proves that she was killed
outside the school premises.

300
00:20:24,288 --> 00:20:25,247
So the question is,

301
00:20:25,248 --> 00:20:28,917
how did she get out of the school
without being caught on CCTV footage?

302
00:20:29,626 --> 00:20:31,712
Around 4:12 p.m.,

303
00:20:32,045 --> 00:20:35,048
Hector received a text from Faye

304
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:38,385
saying she was on her way
to the parking lot.

305
00:20:38,927 --> 00:20:42,514
She was really on her way
to their meeting spot.

306
00:20:49,438 --> 00:20:53,190
Security camera at the front gate
only captures those students

307
00:20:53,191 --> 00:20:56,194
who are entering and leaving
the campus on foot.

308
00:20:56,903 --> 00:21:00,323
The fact that Faye
did not appear on the footage

309
00:21:00,324 --> 00:21:01,616
only means one thing,

310
00:21:02,075 --> 00:21:04,328
she did not walk out of the campus.

311
00:21:04,703 --> 00:21:08,540
Someone snuck her out of school
through an unsuspicious method.

312
00:21:16,048 --> 00:21:17,174
In the car!

313
00:21:18,175 --> 00:21:19,926
Because they used a different exit.

314
00:21:20,427 --> 00:21:21,427
Right!

315
00:21:22,012 --> 00:21:23,012
You mentioned that the victim

316
00:21:23,013 --> 00:21:25,390
was supposed to meet the suspect
in the parking lot.

317
00:21:27,184 --> 00:21:28,852
Everything seems to make sense now.

318
00:21:36,485 --> 00:21:41,238
The suspect didn’t need
to force the victim into the car

319
00:21:41,239 --> 00:21:43,408
because she went in voluntarily.

320
00:21:43,784 --> 00:21:45,659
So no one suspected him,

321
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:48,330
especially since Hector’s car
was tinted as well.

322
00:21:51,458 --> 00:21:55,087
But how do we explain
the text message Hector received

323
00:21:55,379 --> 00:21:57,214
around 4:50 p.m.?

324
00:21:57,464 --> 00:22:00,132
That message was meant
to establish an alibi,

325
00:22:00,133 --> 00:22:03,762
or at least, reduce the suspicion
anyone might have on him.

326
00:22:04,179 --> 00:22:06,139
Maybe it could be sleeping gas in the car,

327
00:22:06,723 --> 00:22:10,394
or a substance to make the victim
unconscious while he waits.

328
00:22:31,540 --> 00:22:33,583
So the message was fake?

329
00:22:34,167 --> 00:22:35,167
Yes!

330
00:22:36,002 --> 00:22:37,796
When he knew the victim was sleeping,

331
00:22:38,296 --> 00:22:41,341
he took her phone and messaged himself.

332
00:22:42,092 --> 00:22:45,344
He probably waited until dark
before bringing the victim

333
00:22:45,345 --> 00:22:48,515
to the abandoned building
meters away from school.

334
00:22:49,099 --> 00:22:50,809
So what do we do now?

335
00:22:51,351 --> 00:22:53,186
Should we tell the police?

336
00:22:53,812 --> 00:22:57,816
I mean, we have an idea
how Hector got Faye out,

337
00:22:58,150 --> 00:23:00,068
but we don’t have any evidence.

338
00:23:00,777 --> 00:23:02,904
Don’t forget about his connections too.

339
00:23:04,281 --> 00:23:05,866
He’s the mayor’s nephew.

340
00:23:08,201 --> 00:23:11,662
If we are to make an accusation
of a crime this serious,

341
00:23:11,663 --> 00:23:13,290
we must have hard proof.

342
00:23:13,623 --> 00:23:17,669
Then let’s go to the abandoned building,
so we can get some evidence.

343
00:23:18,003 --> 00:23:21,214
I don’t think he’s a fool to leave
any traces in the crime scene.

344
00:23:21,673 --> 00:23:24,634
I don’t think there’s nothing to be found
in that abandoned building.

345
00:23:24,968 --> 00:23:26,136
Because if there was,

346
00:23:26,761 --> 00:23:28,680
the police should’ve already found it.

347
00:23:28,972 --> 00:23:30,307
So what’s the solution?

348
00:23:31,308 --> 00:23:33,768
How do we find concrete evidence?

349
00:23:34,394 --> 00:23:36,271
We’re not gonna look for evidence...

350
00:23:37,189 --> 00:23:38,440
we’re gonna produce it.

351
00:23:38,857 --> 00:23:39,941
Produce it?

352
00:23:40,358 --> 00:23:41,902
How do we do that?

353
00:23:43,069 --> 00:23:44,654
You know what gaslighting is?

354
00:23:45,363 --> 00:23:48,908
It’s a form of psychological abuse
where we present false information

355
00:23:48,909 --> 00:23:50,494
to disorient our target.

356
00:23:51,119 --> 00:23:54,039
Now, Hector believes his crime is perfect,

357
00:23:54,956 --> 00:23:56,541
but what if we tell him it isn’t?

358
00:23:57,417 --> 00:23:58,626
He would doubt his memory

359
00:23:58,627 --> 00:24:01,671
and he would be forced to do something
that we can take advantage of.

360
00:24:04,299 --> 00:24:06,759
As expected from you, Loki.

361
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:09,054
You’re really brilliant!

362
00:24:10,347 --> 00:24:12,307
You quickly figured out a way.

363
00:24:13,350 --> 00:24:14,809
Did you get Hector’s number?

364
00:24:17,562 --> 00:24:21,399
0-9-0-5-3-3-1-4-6-8-4.

365
00:24:23,902 --> 00:24:26,446
I’ll message you later
about our next moves.

366
00:24:27,113 --> 00:24:28,113
For now,

367
00:24:28,323 --> 00:24:30,033
let’s go to our respective classes.

368
00:24:54,307 --> 00:24:57,644
Let's meet up at 4:30 p.m.
at the abandoned building.

369
00:25:17,706 --> 00:25:18,706
Wait.

370
00:25:20,125 --> 00:25:23,211
Can you at least share with us
what your plan really is?

371
00:25:33,138 --> 00:25:37,726
After reading this, he’d probably panic
and rush to the crime scene.

372
00:25:39,227 --> 00:25:41,479
Which means he's really guilty.

373
00:25:42,522 --> 00:25:46,318
But would going back there
be enough evidence, if ever?

374
00:25:46,624 --> 00:25:47,611
Don’t worry.

375
00:25:48,243 --> 00:25:49,244
I have a plan.

376
00:25:50,196 --> 00:25:51,531
Listen to me.

377
00:25:53,353 --> 00:25:55,104
We’ll find out soon enough.

378
00:25:55,577 --> 00:25:56,578
Let's go.

379
00:25:59,664 --> 00:26:03,001
Now, all we have to do
is wait for our prey.

380
00:26:48,254 --> 00:26:50,090
Let’s hide! Hurry! Let’s hide!

381
00:27:35,418 --> 00:27:36,419
Start recording.

382
00:27:37,053 --> 00:27:38,054
Okay.

383
00:27:52,193 --> 00:27:53,793
Is this what you’re looking for, Nestor?

384
00:27:54,446 --> 00:27:57,115
It’s Hector, Loki. Not Nestor!

385
00:27:57,449 --> 00:27:59,784
- My God!
- Isn’t that an execom badge?

386
00:28:00,243 --> 00:28:03,329
I also saw one like that
on Margarette, on her lapel.

387
00:28:03,371 --> 00:28:05,415
I got this while I was investigating here.

388
00:28:06,124 --> 00:28:07,584
I believe this is yours.

389
00:28:12,130 --> 00:28:16,259
Wait, you’re Loki
from the Q.E.D. Club, right?

390
00:28:18,678 --> 00:28:21,806
And you were with those two girls
who talked to me earlier.

391
00:28:23,224 --> 00:28:24,684
Now we have the proof.

392
00:28:26,186 --> 00:28:29,439
Huh? Wait, you’re mistaken.

393
00:28:30,732 --> 00:28:32,650
This badge isn’t mine.

394
00:28:33,234 --> 00:28:36,112
I actually left mine at my house and...

395
00:28:36,446 --> 00:28:37,946
I wasn’t even carrying it when I came...

396
00:28:37,947 --> 00:28:40,992
So you’re saying you were the one
who brought Faye here and burned her?

397
00:28:41,826 --> 00:28:43,870
Do you think this is enough, huh?

398
00:28:45,079 --> 00:28:48,916
To pin the crime
you’re accusing me of on me?

399
00:28:48,917 --> 00:28:50,376
That slip of the tongue?

400
00:28:51,211 --> 00:28:52,212
No.

401
00:28:53,421 --> 00:28:54,631
But this.

402
00:28:55,715 --> 00:28:57,550
This badge has your fingerprint now.

403
00:28:58,384 --> 00:29:00,719
I can already report this
to the campus police that I found it

404
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:02,931
while investigating the crime scene.

405
00:29:04,182 --> 00:29:08,228
This will confirm
that you are suspect number 1.

406
00:29:09,687 --> 00:29:13,316
Imagine the scandal
that it can cause to your family.

407
00:29:13,983 --> 00:29:16,820
Oh, my God! That’s amazing!

408
00:29:18,988 --> 00:29:21,741
He was able to produce evidence.

409
00:29:23,576 --> 00:29:26,329
The police
will definitely investigate this.

410
00:29:26,621 --> 00:29:31,626
They will no doubt find your fingerprints
since you revisited the crime scene.

411
00:29:36,756 --> 00:29:38,590
We've also recorded you coming in

412
00:29:38,591 --> 00:29:41,135
through our...

413
00:29:42,387 --> 00:29:45,348
cleverly concealed camera.

414
00:29:45,640 --> 00:29:46,933
So if I were you,

415
00:29:47,809 --> 00:29:49,394
I’d surrender.

416
00:29:50,103 --> 00:29:51,688
It's game over now.

417
00:29:55,191 --> 00:29:57,569
Even whatever you say to me,

418
00:29:57,861 --> 00:29:59,946
in the end it won’t really matter anyway.

419
00:30:00,321 --> 00:30:03,867
I mean, It’s your word against mine!

420
00:30:04,075 --> 00:30:06,661
And that badge?

421
00:30:09,372 --> 00:30:11,249
That doesn’t even mean anything.

422
00:30:12,458 --> 00:30:14,419
More or less prove anything.

423
00:30:16,629 --> 00:30:17,839
You can come out now!

424
00:30:30,727 --> 00:30:32,687
We got your confession on record.

425
00:30:34,856 --> 00:30:35,857
Okay!

426
00:30:36,274 --> 00:30:40,111
You’ve got my confession on record.
Fine.

427
00:30:40,445 --> 00:30:44,198
But do you really think
that’s enough evidence?

428
00:30:45,074 --> 00:30:48,035
I can easily evade that kind of evidence,

429
00:30:48,036 --> 00:30:50,788
especially now that AI is everywhere.

430
00:30:51,831 --> 00:30:53,791
Well, maybe...

431
00:30:54,500 --> 00:30:55,627
maybe you’re right.

432
00:30:55,877 --> 00:30:59,714
But the video of you revisiting this area.

433
00:30:59,881 --> 00:31:01,840
Plus your fingerprints.

434
00:31:01,841 --> 00:31:04,844
You don’t think
that’s enough evidence for us?

435
00:31:07,597 --> 00:31:10,183
You know, they warned me about you.

436
00:31:10,642 --> 00:31:12,810
But I didn’t listen.

437
00:31:13,227 --> 00:31:14,729
Who warned you about me?

438
00:31:15,688 --> 00:31:17,815
I know you already know who it is.

439
00:31:18,149 --> 00:31:19,984
Do you still want me to say the name?

440
00:31:20,693 --> 00:31:23,780
It’s Moriarty.

441
00:31:25,573 --> 00:31:27,241
Did he order you to do this?

442
00:31:27,617 --> 00:31:30,078
To burn your own girlfriend?

443
00:31:31,204 --> 00:31:33,164
That’s her fault anyway!

444
00:31:34,123 --> 00:31:36,668
She got too close to me, didn’t she?

445
00:31:38,086 --> 00:31:39,169
If she hadn’t done that,

446
00:31:39,170 --> 00:31:42,924
then I probably wouldn’t
have done this either.

447
00:31:43,508 --> 00:31:44,926
That’s on her,

448
00:31:45,426 --> 00:31:46,844
not on me.

449
00:31:48,221 --> 00:31:51,140
Our relationship was an illusion.

450
00:31:51,724 --> 00:31:55,311
A lie, to get her closer to me.

451
00:31:55,770 --> 00:31:59,357
Too bad, I really did fall for her.

452
00:31:59,607 --> 00:32:01,693
But recently,

453
00:32:02,068 --> 00:32:05,070
I found out the execom’s investigating me

454
00:32:05,071 --> 00:32:10,158
because of my connection
to Daniel Geronimo.

455
00:32:10,159 --> 00:32:11,995
That name sounds familiar, doesn’t it?

456
00:32:12,870 --> 00:32:17,291
I found out the execom used Faye
to keep an eye on me.

457
00:32:17,917 --> 00:32:20,211
That’s what really pissed me off.

458
00:32:20,586 --> 00:32:25,008
So I decided to get back at them.

459
00:32:30,388 --> 00:32:33,599
I didn’t tell Faye right away
that I knew the truth.

460
00:32:33,975 --> 00:32:38,521
I pretended
I was completely in love with her.

461
00:32:39,022 --> 00:32:41,940
And once I earned her trust,

462
00:32:41,941 --> 00:32:44,902
I carried out my dark plan.

463
00:32:46,279 --> 00:32:48,614
Simple as that.

464
00:34:17,829 --> 00:34:20,498
I had to do it, because if I didn’t,

465
00:34:21,124 --> 00:34:23,167
you might’ve already heard I’m dead.

466
00:34:24,418 --> 00:34:27,088
He eleminates those who fail him.

467
00:34:27,630 --> 00:34:30,091
He doesn’t leave loose ends, huh?

468
00:34:31,217 --> 00:34:33,052
That Moriarty.

469
00:34:33,469 --> 00:34:35,555
I actually agree with that.

470
00:34:47,316 --> 00:34:52,280
Making a mistake with him
is a huge mistake.

471
00:34:54,198 --> 00:34:55,575
That’s why...

472
00:34:57,660 --> 00:35:00,037
it’s time to die.

473
00:35:09,338 --> 00:35:10,423
Loki!

474
00:35:21,726 --> 00:35:22,935
Jamie!

475
00:35:47,668 --> 00:35:48,920
Hit him, Loki!

476
00:36:42,348 --> 00:36:43,349
No.

477
00:36:45,017 --> 00:36:47,603
- No!
- Die! Die!

478
00:37:08,374 --> 00:37:09,375
Loki!

479
00:37:11,002 --> 00:37:14,338
Loki! Loki! Loki! Loki!

480
00:37:14,505 --> 00:37:15,756
Are you okay?

481
00:37:18,175 --> 00:37:19,385
Didn’t you get hurt?

482
00:37:23,014 --> 00:37:24,348
I just wanna say,

483
00:37:24,890 --> 00:37:26,934
thank you to Lorelei
for your quick reflexes.

484
00:37:29,603 --> 00:37:32,063
But we need to proceed
to the second part of the plan.

485
00:37:32,064 --> 00:37:33,064
Huh?

486
00:37:33,316 --> 00:37:34,442
Wait...

487
00:37:34,692 --> 00:37:37,320
Are we still going to falsify evidence?

488
00:37:37,528 --> 00:37:39,447
Are we going to lie to the police?

489
00:37:39,947 --> 00:37:41,282
I have no choice.

490
00:37:42,867 --> 00:37:46,829
I have to do this to make sure
that criminal ends up in prison.

491
00:37:47,705 --> 00:37:48,956
Because if I don’t,

492
00:37:50,416 --> 00:37:52,710
more victims might end up
because of Moriarty.

493
00:37:53,085 --> 00:37:54,337
- But...
- Lori!

494
00:37:54,503 --> 00:37:56,630
We just have to believe in Loki.

495
00:37:57,131 --> 00:37:59,174
Is that concern more important to you now

496
00:37:59,175 --> 00:38:02,511
than giving justice to Faye’s death?

497
00:38:03,512 --> 00:38:05,431
Sometimes when fighting evil,

498
00:38:06,057 --> 00:38:08,017
the end justifies the means.

499
00:38:09,852 --> 00:38:10,936
Fine.

500
00:38:12,271 --> 00:38:13,564
I trust you.

501
00:38:21,739 --> 00:38:22,782
Hello.

502
00:38:23,324 --> 00:38:24,450
Officer Montreal.

503
00:38:25,159 --> 00:38:27,286
We can’t contact Chief Estrada.

504
00:38:28,245 --> 00:38:29,997
We need you at the crime scene.

505
00:38:30,706 --> 00:38:33,417
We're about to confront the culprit.
Thank you!

506
00:38:35,211 --> 00:38:38,672
Wait, why did you say
we’re only about to confront him?

507
00:38:39,382 --> 00:38:40,883
I don’t have time to explain.

508
00:38:41,258 --> 00:38:42,802
I need you to do something quick.

509
00:38:44,428 --> 00:38:46,597
Alright, sure! What is it?

510
00:38:46,889 --> 00:38:48,557
You girls need to punch me in the face.

511
00:38:48,682 --> 00:38:49,724
- What?
- What?

512
00:38:49,725 --> 00:38:50,810
As hard as you can.

513
00:38:51,185 --> 00:38:52,937
Why would I do that?

514
00:38:53,729 --> 00:38:56,232
We need to show them
that Victor really got to me.

515
00:38:56,357 --> 00:38:58,316
Hector! My God, Loki!

516
00:38:58,317 --> 00:39:00,986
You know, your name blindness
is really getting frustrating!

517
00:39:01,195 --> 00:39:03,739
And what, we’re going to lie
to the police too?

518
00:39:03,989 --> 00:39:05,573
You really don’t listen, do you?

519
00:39:05,574 --> 00:39:07,784
- You’re really getting on my nerves!
- You’re annoyed?

520
00:39:07,785 --> 00:39:08,577
- Are you annoyed?
- Yes!

521
00:39:08,578 --> 00:39:09,744
- I’m really fed up with you!
- Use that!

522
00:39:09,745 --> 00:39:10,945
Come on! Why won’t you hit me?

523
00:39:12,540 --> 00:39:14,041
Lori!

524
00:39:15,960 --> 00:39:18,295
Loki, are you okay?

525
00:39:22,007 --> 00:39:23,467
Oh, what happened here?

526
00:39:26,554 --> 00:39:28,973
Chief, we were supposed
to confront about his crime.

527
00:39:30,015 --> 00:39:31,724
But he attacked first,

528
00:39:31,725 --> 00:39:35,146
and he was even carrying
a butterfly knife.

529
00:39:36,188 --> 00:39:38,858
Good thing, we got ahead of him.

530
00:39:39,275 --> 00:39:41,986
Besides, we have all
the evidence against him.

531
00:39:44,071 --> 00:39:47,908
As far as I know, I was asking you
for help in investigating.

532
00:39:48,242 --> 00:39:51,244
- Faye Figueroa’s death.
- Sir, excuse me.

533
00:39:51,245 --> 00:39:52,745
But I didn’t expect you

534
00:39:52,746 --> 00:39:54,873
- to go as far as confronting...
- Come with me.

535
00:39:54,874 --> 00:39:57,042
the suspect on your own.

536
00:39:58,502 --> 00:40:04,091
You shouldn’t do things
without us knowing.

537
00:40:04,175 --> 00:40:06,510
What if you got into danger, huh?

538
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:10,264
Chief, I’m the one apologizing
on their behalf.

539
00:40:10,598 --> 00:40:13,350
They did make a big help
to the case, though.

540
00:40:16,395 --> 00:40:18,981
Alright. I’ll head upstairs first.

541
00:40:19,648 --> 00:40:22,109
I’ll look for supporting evidence.

542
00:40:22,359 --> 00:40:25,571
Officer Montreal,
I’ll leave the kids to you.

543
00:40:29,283 --> 00:40:30,451
Are you okay?

544
00:40:31,076 --> 00:40:32,495
We’re okay, officer.

545
00:40:32,703 --> 00:40:34,121
Officer...

546
00:40:34,538 --> 00:40:37,541
can I borrow your phone for a moment?

547
00:40:37,708 --> 00:40:39,710
I need to send a text.

548
00:40:39,919 --> 00:40:42,420
People at home
are probably starting to worry

549
00:40:42,421 --> 00:40:44,423
because I haven’t gone home yet.

550
00:40:44,673 --> 00:40:46,467
Don’t you have a cellphone?

551
00:40:47,927 --> 00:40:50,262
My phone got broken.

552
00:40:50,429 --> 00:40:53,432
Because of the intense confrontation
earlier.

553
00:40:53,599 --> 00:40:58,687
Lori left hers in the Q.E.D. clubroom
because she was in a hurry.

554
00:41:01,315 --> 00:41:02,315
Alright.

555
00:41:15,204 --> 00:41:16,497
What happened here?

556
00:41:20,292 --> 00:41:21,418
Did you get it?

557
00:41:22,795 --> 00:41:25,214
There were ten numbers in his call log.

558
00:41:29,718 --> 00:41:31,303
Wait, wait. Lori, wait.

559
00:41:50,739 --> 00:41:51,699
Is it okay now?

560
00:41:51,808 --> 00:41:54,059
- Have you called it already?
- Thank you, officer.

561
00:41:54,827 --> 00:41:57,788
Alright. Take care next time, okay?

562
00:41:58,038 --> 00:41:59,163
Yes.

563
00:41:59,164 --> 00:42:00,749
Thank you.

564
00:42:33,568 --> 00:42:36,194
Can deception ever
justify the pursuit of truth?

565
00:42:36,368 --> 00:42:40,163
Do you realize, Loki,
that you just cut loose the thread

566
00:42:40,164 --> 00:42:44,627
that could’ve led them to the mystery man?

567
00:42:45,044 --> 00:42:46,670
We’re clearly busy at the moment.

568
00:42:47,004 --> 00:42:51,633
I just wanted to ask
if Jamie passed by here.

569
00:42:51,634 --> 00:42:54,720
All the execom and campus police
are searching the school buildings.

570
00:42:55,846 --> 00:42:57,306
Let’s try cracking the code again.

571
00:42:57,556 --> 00:43:00,768
And if you want to prevent
another victim of Moriarty...

572
00:43:01,393 --> 00:43:06,732
I suggest, you stop muttering
and give us the urgent help we need.

573
00:43:09,109 --> 00:43:11,737
We have to see for ourselves
if Jamie is really out there.

574
00:43:12,446 --> 00:43:13,447
Come on!
